I have implemented a fix for this problem. The app.js code should call a method app.prepareIcons(['content/icons/32.png'],function(err, iconList) {
     var statusIcon = app.createStatusIcon({
          icon:iconList['content/icons/32.png'],
          tooltip:'AppJS Hello World',
          menu:trayMenu
        });

});
iconList is a hashmap that returns the full path to a file so you can pass that into the c++ code. Internally when running packages appjs extracts the icons to a cache directory and uses a sha1 to name the file (to avoid duplicates). So when running inside a package file you would have to explicitly call the prepareIcons function. We can just add that function call to all of the examples on the website and the documentation and it should not cause any problems.
